ge nach, ob und inwiefern die Poetik-Rezeption dieser Zeit tatsächlich, wie meist behauptet, eine ‚rationalistische‘ bzw. ‚moralistische‘ Umdeutung der Aristotelischen Theorie darstellt.  aThe engagement with Aristotle’s newly rediscovered Poetics is fundamental to the beginnings of modern literary theory in 16th century Italy. Based on present-day research into Aristotle, Brigitte Kappl takes central themes from the Poetics (poetry as imitation, action and character, tragic flaw, cathartic effect) to examine whether and to what extent the literary theory of that age actually presents a ‘rationalistic’ or ‘moralistic’ re-interpretation of Aristotle’s theory, as is usually maintained.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCriticismzItalyxHistoryy16th century. 0aPoeticsxHistoryy16th century. 4aAntikerezeption. 4aPoetik. 4aRenaissance. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aPoetics.  aRenaissance.  areception of Antiquity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2006z9783110277128oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2006z9783110276992oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311018952040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089285740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110892857423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110892857/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2006  aZDB-23-DGGb2006  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014